    Class Description
    Ack
    Message-Class, which is sent at the beginning of a Message[] inside the MessageStructure from the server to the client who has sent the request which was processed and accepted by the server
    ActionType
    Enum for all the different types of actions that can be performed.
    Attachment
    This class is used to attach a MessageType and a profile to a WebSocket in the NetworkHandler.
    Attackable
    Interface for all things that can be attacked
    BasicMessage
    BasicMessage is one of the Message Types, which other communication.messages extend from.
    CharacterConfig
    This class is used to parse the JSON file containing the character configuration.
    CharacterSelection
    CharacterSelection is used by the Client to respond to the servers GameAssignment message.
    ConfigHero
    This class is used to parse the JSON character config which contains an array of these characters.
    Configuration
    This class parses and stores the configuration files (scenario, character and match configuration).
    ConfigurationTest
    Tests for the class Configuration, which reads the configuration files.
    ConfirmSelection
    ConfirmSelection is sent by the Server to the first client, which CharacterSelection the server received first, and informs it that the server received and accepted its CharacterSelection.
    ConsumedAPEvent
    This message is sent when a character consumes AP (e.g. character performs a melee attack)
    ConsumedMPEvent
    This message is sent when a character consumes MP (e.g. character moves)
    Controller
    The Controller implements the game logic and alters the game model.
    ControllerTest
    Test class for some of the controller methods.
    DestroyedEntityEvent
    This message is sent when an entity is removed from the map.
    DisconnectEvent
    This message lets the client know that the servers next move will be disconnecting the client.
    DisconnectRequest
    Message-Class, which is responsible to send DisconnectRequests to the server if the user wants to disconnect from the server
    EndRoundRequest
    Message-Class, which is responsible to send EndRoundRequests to the server if the user wants to stop a turn with his character before the turn officially ends
    Entities
    abstract class to represent different entities (Rock, InGameCharacter, NPC and InfinityStone extend from it)

    Message-Class, which is responsible for Error-Messages sent by the server

    ExchangeInfinityStoneEvent
    Message-Class, which is responsible to send ExchangeInfinityStoneEvents to the clients if the user wants one of his characters to exchange an Infinity Stone with another character and this was approved by the server to do so
    ExchangeInfinityStoneRequest
    Message-Class, which is responsible to send ExchangeInfinityStoneRequests to the server if the user wants one of his characters to exchange an Infinity Stone with another character of his team
    ExtractorEntities
    The ExtractorEntities class is used to extract all objects, which are subclasses of Entities in case they are stored in an EntitiesArray.
    ExtractorGamestateEvent
    Message-Class, which is sent at the end of EACH AND EVERY message from the server to inform the client about the current GameState on the map
    ExtractorMessage
    The ExtractorMessage class is used to extract all objects, which are subclasses of Message in case they are stored in an MessageArray (for Example in a MessageStructure object).
    ExtractorMessageStructure  
    ExtractorMessageType
    This class is needed to distinguish the message types of incoming messages with a switch case in the onMessage method.

    GameAssignment

    GamestateEvent
    Message-Class, which is sent at the end of EACH AND EVERY message from the server to inform the client about the current GameState on the map
    GameStructure
    This message is sent to all to the server connected clients once both clients have decided on their teams.
    GeneralAssignment
    GeneralAssignment is used by the Server if a client joined a game as spectator or a player rejoins his game.
    GoodbyeClient
    GoodbyeClient is used to close a server-connection if a few conditions are given.
    Goose

    MeleeAttackRequest
    Message-Class, which is responsible to send MeleeAttackRequests to the server if the user wants to do an melee attack
